# Unbalanced hierarchy fixture for --preferred-number-of-levels (issue #308).
#
# Plain weighted edge list (source target weight), like ninetriangles.net.
# Two regions joined by a single weak bridge:
#   * Shallow region (nodes 1..9): three tightly-knit triangles with strong
#     intra-triangle weights and weak inter-triangle links. Most of the flow
#     lives here and it resolves into a flat, shallow module structure.
#   * Deep region (nodes 10..36): a ninetriangles-style nested triangles-of-
#     triangles built from low-weight links, which the optimizer refines into
#     several nested levels.
#
# The result is an unbalanced tree: a shallow branch carrying most of the flow
# and one deep branch. Used to check that shallower depth steering collapses the
# deep branch reliably while the off-path output stays byte-identical to master.
*Edges
# --- shallow region: three heavy triangles, weakly linked ---
1 2 10
1 3 10
2 3 10
4 5 10
4 6 10
5 6 10
7 8 10
7 9 10
8 9 10
3 4 0.3
6 7 0.3
9 1 0.3
